{{Infobox baseball biography |name=Ham Deok-ju |position=[[Pitcher (baseball)|Pitcher]] |team=Doosan Bears |number=1 |bats=Left |throws=Left |birth_date={{Birth date and age|1995|1|13|df=y}} |debutleague=[[Korean Baseball Organization|KBO]] |debutyear=2013 |debutteam=[[Doosan Bears]] |statyear=2018 season |statleague=KBO |stat1label=[[Win–loss record (pitching)|Win–loss record]] |stat1value=23–13 |stat2label=[[Earned run average]] |stat2value=3.78 |stat3label=[[Strikeout]]s |stat3value=322 |teams= *[[Doosan Bears]] ({{by|2013}}–present) }}
'''Ham Deok-ju''' ({{korean|hangul=함덕주}} [[Hanja]]: 咸德柱; born 13 January 1995) is a South Korean professional baseball pitcher who is currently playing for the [[Doosan Bears]] of the [[Korea Baseball Organization]].
He graduated from Wonju High School and was selected to Doosan Bears by a draft in 2013 (2nd draft, 5th round). In 2018, he changed back number from No.61 to No.1. He achieved his personal best of nine wins in 2017 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.koreabaseball.com/Record/Player/PitcherDetail/Basic.aspx?playerId=63248|title=KBO 홈페이지 Player info|last=스포츠투아이|first=|date=|website=KBO|language=ko|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 April 2018}}</ref>
He represented [[South Korea national baseball team|South Korea]] at the [[Baseball at the 2018 Asian Games|2018 Asian Games]].<ref>{{cite news |title=2018 자카르타-팔렘방 아시안게임 야구 국가대표팀 최종 엔트리 확정 |url=https://www.koreabaseball.com/News/Notice/View.aspx?bdSe=7042 |language=ko |publisher=[[Korea Baseball Organization]] |date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=August 29, 2018}}</ref>
